title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
Hi!


I have this PCB without traces of humidity but it does't turn on:

- PP5V_SUS: 0V (not short)

Greetings and thanks.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message: Do you get 3V3_SUS?

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
Thanks for replying [USER=682]@2informaticos[/USER] .

No, I don't have PP3V3_SUS.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
Missing PM_SLP_SUS_L too?
Confirm that.

Check SMC_BATLOW_L.
Be sure to use original 60/85W Magsafe 2 charger.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
Yes,  PM_SLP_SUS_L = 0.00V. 

SMC_BATLOW_L = 3.30V.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message: Now check PCH_DSWVRMEN, PM_DSW_PWRGD and all PCH's (DC) RTC signals.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
PCH_DSWVRMEN = 3.23V
PM_DSW_PWRGD = 0.00V
RTC_RESET_L = 3.33V
PCH_SRTCRST_L = 3.33V
PCH_INTRUDER_L = 3.07V
PCH_INTVRMEN_L = 3.25V
PPVRTC_G3_PCH = 3.34V

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
"PM_DSW_PWRGD = 0.00V"
What about S5_PWRGD?

Check R5092...

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
"What about S5_PWRGD?"
It is on R7941.

I said to check R5092 for other reason; it controls SMC_S5_PWRGD_VIN.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message: S5_PWRGD = 0.055V

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
"It is on R7941."
You've checked voltage on both pins of R5092 before; why not this time?

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
Remove resistor and check its ohm value.
If 3V3_S5 (L7260) is present, then pin 2 of R7941 MUST go high.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
R7941= 99.8K ohms.

Yes, 3V3_S5 is present on L7260.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
Try cutting off the trace to U7201, pin 20.
Choose a point where you can recover the trace later.

You can also try changing U7201 instead.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message: I have cut the trace, I have changed U7201 and still the same.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
S5_PWRGD goes high, once trace is cutted off?
R7941 must be kept in place.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
R7941:
- pin 1: 3.43V
- pin 2: 0.055V 

R7941 is in place.

title: 820-3462 no PP5V_SUS
message:
SMC problem; it pulls down the signal.
Try reballing it first.
May need to change it.
